.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-7-18::.
The people use 6 different means of transport: airplane, quad-bike, boat, jet-ski, skateboard, train
6 different brands of cigars are smoked: baccarat, old-henry, pall-mall, siglo, tiparillo, dannemann
 1. the person driving the airplane is on the left of the person driving the jet-ski##1
 2. the old-henry-smoker is the person driving the train##1
 3. the person driving the boat is on the left or right of the person driving the jet-ski##3
 4. the person driving the quad-bike is somewhere between the person driving the boat and the dannemann-smoker##7
 5. the person driving the jet-ski is somewhere between the person driving the airplane and the person driving the quad-bike##7
 6. the person driving the skateboard is somewhere to the right of the person driving the boat##5
 7. the person driving the skateboard is on the right of the tiparillo-smoker##1
 8. the person driving the boat is on the right of the person driving the jet-ski##1
 9. the person driving the train is somewhere to the right of the person driving the airplane##5
10. the baccarat-smoker is in an even position##4
11. the person driving the quad-bike is on the left or right of the pall-mall-smoker##3
12. the person driving the train is somewhere to the right of the baccarat-smoker##5
13. the pall-mall-smoker is on the left of the tiparillo-smoker##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |    2     |    3     |     4      |       5       |    6     |
| Transport   | airplane | jet-ski | boat   | quad-bike  | skateboard      | train  |
| Cigar         | siglo      | baccarat | pall-mall | tiparillo | dannemann | old-henry |

